15:12.445 --> 15:16.183
It's just, I can't stop
thinking, you know...

15:16.216 --> 15:18.285
What does it mean
that they kept us here?

15:18.318 --> 15:20.587
It means we're the best.

15:20.620 --> 15:23.656
Out of 3000 guys? Come on, Len.
We're just tokens, man.

15:23.690 --> 15:25.225
You know, Philbert,

15:25.258 --> 15:28.028
you're in a real shitty mood
today, man.

15:33.266 --> 15:36.303
That... That video
you were talking about...

15:36.336 --> 15:37.637
I saw it too.

15:37.670 --> 15:40.007
You saw it,
the "kill everybody else" thing?

15:40.040 --> 15:42.009
It's crazy.
I mean, it's fucking scary

15:42.042 --> 15:45.012
is what is, Ed. It's got me--
Shh. Shh, shh.

15:45.045 --> 15:49.082
Easy. Yeah, relax.

15:49.116 --> 15:53.086
This political stuff,
don't take it so seriously.

15:53.120 --> 15:55.755
It doesn't mean anything.
Just lay off.

15:55.788 --> 15:58.225
Go have some fun
or something.

15:58.258 --> 16:00.027
It's all this
shit they're saying.

16:00.060 --> 16:02.295
Those idiots say anything.
It isn't real.

16:02.329 --> 16:03.997
All right?
It's just entertainment,

16:04.031 --> 16:05.598
that's all it is.

16:07.500 --> 16:09.169
Speaking of entertainment,

16:09.202 --> 16:12.139
did you check out
that cheese gal

16:12.172 --> 16:13.406
like we were telling you?

16:13.440 --> 16:15.075
Yeah, I did. It's stupid.

16:15.108 --> 16:17.144
I mean,
it's not like you can touch her.

16:17.177 --> 16:20.747
Oh, yeah? The optics
can take you a long way.

16:20.780 --> 16:22.615
Don't be so tactile,
my friend.

16:22.649 --> 16:25.218
[***]

16:25.252 --> 16:27.520
Hang in there, old-timer.

16:27.554 --> 16:29.189
Thanks, Ed.

16:40.500 --> 16:44.571
MAN [OVER PA]:
This is Washington and Wells.

16:44.604 --> 16:49.742
Transfer to Orange Line trains
at Washington and Wells.

16:49.776 --> 16:54.047
This is a Pink Line train
to 54th and Cermak.

17:01.454 --> 17:03.190
[BEEPS]

17:03.223 --> 17:05.525
I think it's more
anti-establishment sentiment

17:05.558 --> 17:08.528
than any real agenda against
a so-called "Other"--

17:08.561 --> 17:10.163
MAN [OVER TV]:
That's a fair point.

17:10.197 --> 17:12.165
Yes. Finally somebody's
talking about it.

17:12.199 --> 17:14.701
As you know, we have to kill
all others. At the same--

17:14.734 --> 17:17.704
Well, obviously, the Candidate
isn't speaking literally.

17:17.737 --> 17:19.672
This is just about ideas.
He's lying.

17:19.706 --> 17:21.040
I think--

17:27.580 --> 17:31.518
[***]

17:33.386 --> 17:35.255
Hey.

17:35.288 --> 17:37.757
What happened?

17:37.790 --> 17:39.492
Hey.

17:41.494 --> 17:43.130
Hey.

17:44.597 --> 17:47.134
Hey, somebody's in here.

17:49.669 --> 17:51.604
Hey,
somebody's still in here.

17:53.206 --> 17:54.707
Hey, guys.
MAN [OVER PA]: Yes,

17:54.741 --> 17:56.376
we are working on it, Philbert.
Who is this?

17:56.409 --> 17:57.544
[***]

18:05.818 --> 18:07.854
[THUD, TRAIN ENGINE WHIRS]

18:23.636 --> 18:24.771
[SHUTTERING CLICKING]

18:28.575 --> 18:30.677
Stop. Aah! Unh.

18:30.710 --> 18:31.844
[***]

18:35.515 --> 18:36.649
[GRUNTS]

18:37.517 --> 18:41.421
[***]

18:51.264 --> 18:55.502
SERGEANT:
Did you feel yourself or others
in immediate danger?

18:55.535 --> 18:58.638
No. I mean, yeah...

18:58.671 --> 19:01.574
It's-- Bef--
Before the train was--

19:01.608 --> 19:04.211
Was sketchy.
Sketchy?

19:04.244 --> 19:08.548
Mechanically? You know--
I mean, it had stopped.

19:08.581 --> 19:09.882
Frozen, that's the word.

19:09.916 --> 19:11.651
It had frozen
just moments before,

19:11.684 --> 19:13.353
but we went past this sign--

19:13.386 --> 19:16.589
Trancom reports that there was
a brief power fail.

19:16.623 --> 19:18.425
Yeah, well, it wasn't brief,
it was more--

19:18.458 --> 19:21.428
In this brief power failure, you
were frightened to the point

19:21.461 --> 19:24.831
you engaged the emergency
braking system?

19:24.864 --> 19:26.733
Well, no,

19:26.766 --> 19:28.601
that was because of the sign,
which I--

19:28.635 --> 19:30.703
A sign told you
to stop the train?

19:30.737 --> 19:32.672
No, of course not. Look,

19:32.705 --> 19:35.375
I'm not crazy, okay?

19:35.408 --> 19:38.445
I'm not crazy, I--

19:38.478 --> 19:41.548
Some hackers
must have gotten to it.

19:41.581 --> 19:43.216
It was terrible,

19:43.250 --> 19:45.585
and I just wanted
to get a better look. It was--

19:47.954 --> 19:50.557
It was hate speech.

19:50.590 --> 19:52.559
It said to...

19:52.592 --> 19:55.695
"kill all others"
in giant letters.

19:57.597 --> 20:00.400
Isn't that some sort of crime
or something? I mean, it--

20:01.934 --> 20:04.904
It's very dangerous.

20:04.937 --> 20:07.440
SERGEANT:
How does the water feel?

20:10.877 --> 20:12.245
Fast.

20:13.580 --> 20:15.248
Soothing.

20:15.282 --> 20:18.685
The sensors usually override
erroneous user input.

20:18.718 --> 20:20.820
However,
in your case it stopped.

20:20.853 --> 20:22.589
Yeah,
because it was dangerous.

20:22.622 --> 20:26.326
Causing the train pod
behind yours to crash into you.

20:28.861 --> 20:31.564
Crashed? I crashed a train?
Rarely happens.

20:31.598 --> 20:33.966
And rare would really be
an overstatement.

20:34.000 --> 20:35.702
Never would be
more accurate.

20:35.735 --> 20:39.339
Train incidents, they
don't really happen anymore.

20:39.372 --> 20:43.276
Auto-piloting rules out
human error. Same for COVs.

20:43.310 --> 20:46.579
Except of course,
the occasional outliers.

20:46.613 --> 20:48.515
Drugs, chemicals,

20:48.548 --> 20:50.583
those can create outliers.

20:50.617 --> 20:52.419
I wasn't drinking.
I wasn't on anything.

20:52.452 --> 20:54.020
I was just--

20:54.053 --> 20:56.623
I was just concerned,
that's all.

20:57.757 --> 20:59.526
So you weren't.

21:01.093 --> 21:02.429
He's all clean.

21:04.631 --> 21:06.466
ADJUSTER: Thank you.
Mm.

21:09.369 --> 21:13.373
SERGEANT:
Nevertheless, Trancom does not
want you back on their system.

21:13.406 --> 21:16.609
Temporarily.
Yeah.

21:16.643 --> 21:18.645
ADJUSTER:
This conversation
will be recorded

21:18.678 --> 21:21.314
for documentation purposes.

21:21.348 --> 21:25.585
Consent?
Yeah. Yup. Yes.

21:25.618 --> 21:27.554
[GLASSES BEEP]

21:29.121 --> 21:31.724
Now that we've established
the situational facts,

21:31.758 --> 21:36.028
we now are going to assess
the predispositional factors.

21:36.062 --> 21:37.764
What? I'm not really clear--

21:37.797 --> 21:39.532
A simple yes or no is fine.

21:39.566 --> 21:43.470
Is everything okay at home?
Yes.

21:43.503 --> 21:47.607
Any recent feelings of anxiety,
depression or paranoia?

21:47.640 --> 21:48.808
No. I told you--

21:48.841 --> 21:50.910
Any unexplained weight loss,

21:50.943 --> 21:52.879
weight gain, sleeplessness,

21:52.912 --> 21:54.113
apathy,
God, no.

21:54.146 --> 21:58.418
obsessive fixations?
No. I'm...

21:58.451 --> 22:01.120
fine.
I remind you that your veracity

22:01.153 --> 22:04.123
in the predispositional
assessment is equally important

22:04.156 --> 22:09.462
to the evaluation of your claim
to the situational assessment.

22:09.496 --> 22:11.531
Can you count
the snowflakes?

22:14.166 --> 22:15.768
No, I'm sorry.
I don't think I can.

22:15.802 --> 22:17.837
Do you see the sheep?

22:19.606 --> 22:21.107
No.

22:21.140 --> 22:24.944
In the upper left-hand corner,
do you see the sheep?

22:29.916 --> 22:33.620
No, I'm sorry.
I don't see these sheep.

22:33.653 --> 22:36.789
Has anything changed
in your psychic environment?

22:36.823 --> 22:39.058
Real or imagined?

22:39.091 --> 22:41.594
In your interpersonal
relationships

22:41.628 --> 22:43.095
or your professional life
that would

22:43.129 --> 22:44.797
impair
your ability to absorb,

22:44.831 --> 22:49.101
process or respond
to the world around you?

22:50.603 --> 22:53.406
What does
"COV provisional" mean?

22:53.440 --> 22:55.041
It means
what it sounds like it means.

22:55.074 --> 22:56.709
No, Philbert, uh-uh,

22:56.743 --> 22:58.478
don't do this.
You don't get to do this--

22:58.511 --> 22:59.712
Fuck, Maggie, please.

22:59.746 --> 23:02.449
Look, I just got in an accident.
Okay?

23:02.482 --> 23:05.017
I didn't even have an accident.
The train did. You know?

23:05.051 --> 23:08.087
I've been interrogated for the
last 3-and-a-half fucking hours.

23:08.120 --> 23:10.557
For an accident
that wasn't even my fault.

23:10.590 --> 23:12.459
No knocks on my license.

23:12.492 --> 23:14.060
But it's provisional
so there's still--

23:14.093 --> 23:15.428
No. It-- They--

23:16.963 --> 23:18.565
Fuck. They just said

23:18.598 --> 23:20.600
I have to stay off
public transit for a while.

23:20.633 --> 23:22.669
They're putting me in a new
computer-operated vehicle.

23:22.702 --> 23:26.673
We don't have to ride
around in this 20-year-old
piece of junk anymore.

23:26.706 --> 23:28.541
No cost to us.

23:28.575 --> 23:32.879
Zero, zip, nada.
Case closed. Okay?

23:36.716 --> 23:38.685
I'm sorry, honey.

23:39.852 --> 23:41.721
Are you all right?

23:43.556 --> 23:46.726
I'll pay better attention
next time.

23:46.759 --> 23:49.829
We can all
just fucking calm down.

23:49.862 --> 23:52.465
It's all going
to be okay.

23:52.499 --> 23:56.836
You're okay, honey.
You're okay.

23:56.869 --> 23:59.939
WOMAN:
Rising sea levels
and increasing temperatures

23:59.972 --> 24:01.841
have long since impacted--

24:01.874 --> 24:04.611
We have to parse it out.
Who dresses these people?

24:04.644 --> 24:06.513
"Kill all others."

24:06.546 --> 24:08.848
What sort of candidate says--
Hear this?

24:08.881 --> 24:11.150
It's unintellectual
and unpolitical.

24:11.183 --> 24:13.653
This is what I've been saying
all along.

24:13.686 --> 24:15.087
...the systemic change
we need.

24:15.121 --> 24:17.123
We'll get into
all of this, folks,

24:17.156 --> 24:18.958
after the break.
[TV BEEPS]

24:20.192 --> 24:22.194
They're saying nothing.

24:23.696 --> 24:25.632
Honey.
They're saying nothing.

24:25.665 --> 24:28.801
Honey, it's all this stuff.
It's too much.

24:28.835 --> 24:31.638
Hey,
I threw out all the coffee.

24:31.671 --> 24:33.072
The coffee?

24:34.306 --> 24:37.176
I threw out all the coffee.

24:37.209 --> 24:39.946
Okay.
And cheese.

24:39.979 --> 24:42.048
It's all my fault.

24:43.082 --> 24:45.518
Off.

24:45.552 --> 24:46.719
It's a distraction.

24:47.687 --> 24:49.088
I'm sorry.

24:49.121 --> 24:53.893
[***]

24:53.926 --> 24:57.096
No more noise. Just us. Off.

24:59.231 --> 25:01.968
Just us.
Okay, babe.

25:07.139 --> 25:08.274
Okay.

25:09.909 --> 25:11.644
Lights.

25:14.180 --> 25:18.117
[***]

25:25.357 --> 25:28.728
I love you, Madge.
I love you too.

25:28.761 --> 25:30.296
Oh, Jesus. Look out.

25:30.329 --> 25:33.633
Ms. Nickels.
PHILBERT: How are you?

25:33.666 --> 25:34.834
Ha, ha.

25:34.867 --> 25:36.135
She's always out there.

25:36.168 --> 25:38.571
It's like she times it
with our exit.

25:38.605 --> 25:42.041
"Let me tell you about
all my problems."

25:42.074 --> 25:43.976
MAN 1:
Don't let her get away.

25:44.010 --> 25:45.612
Heading towards Plimpton Place.

25:45.645 --> 25:47.079
WOMAN 1:
Didn't do anything!

25:47.113 --> 25:48.915
WOMAN 2:
Cut her off!

25:51.017 --> 25:52.184
Scary.

25:52.218 --> 25:53.920
PHILBERT:
Stop the car.

25:53.953 --> 25:55.321
We don't even know what's--

25:55.354 --> 25:57.724
Stop the car.
Philbert!

25:57.757 --> 25:59.358
Hey. What's going on here?
Philbert!

25:59.391 --> 26:00.827
Hey!
Philbert!

26:00.860 --> 26:02.328
[GRUNTING]

26:02.361 --> 26:04.664
Hey. What's going on here?

26:04.697 --> 26:06.365
What's going on here?
[CRYING]

26:06.398 --> 26:08.367
Back off, we got her.
Got her doing what?

26:08.400 --> 26:10.002
MAN 2:
She's an Other. We caught her.

26:10.036 --> 26:11.671
Get off her.

26:11.704 --> 26:13.806
What's the matter?
You can't just attack people.

26:13.840 --> 26:15.374
Corner of Moss and Cherry.
Hurry.

26:15.407 --> 26:16.976
You know her?
No, I don't know her.

26:17.009 --> 26:18.177
Get off of her.

26:18.210 --> 26:19.612
Are you out of your mind?

26:19.646 --> 26:21.614
I'm not going
until the cops get here.

26:21.648 --> 26:22.949
They're on their way, buddy,
so back off.

26:22.982 --> 26:24.617
You back off.

26:24.651 --> 26:26.218
MAN 3:
You don't know
what this is about.

26:26.252 --> 26:27.620
I don't need to. Get off.

26:27.654 --> 26:29.155
Let's go. Now.

26:29.188 --> 26:31.290
If nothing's wrong,
I'm gonna see this through.

26:31.323 --> 26:32.625
Asshole.
We'll report you too.

26:32.659 --> 26:34.060
Call me an asshole
one more time!

26:34.093 --> 26:35.728
Philbert. Philbert.
Call me a fucking asshole!

26:35.762 --> 26:37.697
Watch him, he's one of them.

26:37.730 --> 26:39.666
One of who?
VOICE: Citizen, remain calm.

26:39.699 --> 26:40.833
Hey.

26:43.102 --> 26:44.837
VOICE:
Mr. Noyce, stand back.

26:47.173 --> 26:48.307
[***]

26:55.147 --> 26:57.349
How do you know the suspect?

26:58.450 --> 27:00.319
I-- I didn't--

27:00.352 --> 27:02.388
I didn't see her
as a suspect.

27:02.421 --> 27:04.256
I saw a woman running
down the street.

27:04.290 --> 27:06.425
You think you'd steer clear
of any incidents,

27:06.458 --> 27:08.294
given
that you were just here.

27:10.096 --> 27:11.831
Look, I was literally
on my way to work

27:11.864 --> 27:13.866
when I saw this woman
being chased.

27:13.900 --> 27:19.271
Okay? And it just seemed wrong,
and I just reacted.

27:19.305 --> 27:20.840
Okay?

27:23.009 --> 27:25.177
Are those people
being charged?

27:25.211 --> 27:29.015
Because... I mean,
they assaulted that woman.

27:30.282 --> 27:31.818
I think I know
some of their names.

27:31.851 --> 27:34.053
The big guy, Rick,
tackled that woman.

27:34.086 --> 27:37.690
Look, Mr. Noyce,
I'm not a political gal.

27:37.724 --> 27:40.092
And I do not buy
into the mumbo jumbo

27:40.126 --> 27:42.294
about the Others
and whatnot.

27:42.328 --> 27:45.331
But what I do know
is outliers.

27:45.364 --> 27:48.701
Most people have maybe one,
two interactions with us

27:48.735 --> 27:50.069
over a five-year span.

27:50.102 --> 27:52.905
You've been here twice
in two days.

27:52.939 --> 27:55.908
It starts to look bad.
To form a pattern.

27:55.942 --> 27:58.310
To invite observation.

27:58.344 --> 28:00.446
And under close
enough observation,

28:00.479 --> 28:03.950
maybe anybody can look
a little quirky.

28:03.983 --> 28:06.185
Screwy.

28:06.218 --> 28:08.087
A little Other.

28:12.258 --> 28:14.761
Go to work, Mr. Noyce.

28:16.262 --> 28:17.396
[***]

28:23.002 --> 28:24.804
So luckily,
I wasn't hurt. You know?

28:26.072 --> 28:28.174
Yeah,
but from an HR standpoint,

28:28.207 --> 28:29.976
we still need to do
health monitoring.

28:30.009 --> 28:31.844
Sure.
Thirty days.

28:31.878 --> 28:33.179
Make sure
nothing's wrong.

28:33.212 --> 28:37.283
No underlying health problems,
you know.

28:37.316 --> 28:39.151
I'm curious,
this is for the train accident

28:39.185 --> 28:40.386
or the other thing?

28:41.353 --> 28:43.022
What other thing?

28:44.090 --> 28:45.792
Nothing. I meant-- Nothing.

28:47.326 --> 28:49.495
Need your consent to unlock.

28:49.528 --> 28:51.764
This also gives us consent
to report

28:51.798 --> 28:53.800
your health data
to Human Resources.

28:55.167 --> 28:56.735
Sure.

28:59.538 --> 29:02.909
Boop. There we go.
[MUTTERS]

29:02.942 --> 29:04.343
Go ahead. You can
put it on yourself.

29:04.376 --> 29:06.913
Nothing fancy.
Okay.

29:10.116 --> 29:13.152
So is it for mental health?
Or just for...

29:13.185 --> 29:16.355
Oh. No, no, no,
don't be paranoid.

29:16.388 --> 29:18.925
It's for overall health.

29:18.958 --> 29:23.295
Stress, blood pressure,
blood sugar, cholesterol.

29:23.329 --> 29:25.064
To minimize sick time,

29:25.097 --> 29:27.800
see if you need
any preventative time off.

29:27.834 --> 29:31.203
Yeah. Got you. All right.

29:31.237 --> 29:32.571
Aah.

29:32.604 --> 29:36.008
Yes, it, uh, pinches
a little the first time,

29:36.042 --> 29:38.544
but then
you won't even notice it.

29:38.577 --> 29:40.246
Oh, yeah.

29:40.279 --> 29:41.480
[MONITOR BEEPING]

29:41.513 --> 29:43.049
Yeah.

29:43.082 --> 29:45.818
[BEEPING]

29:45.852 --> 29:49.055
Yeah. So your data
is confidential.

29:49.088 --> 29:51.090
It will only be transmitted
to HR.

29:51.123 --> 29:53.392
That's it?
That's it.

29:53.425 --> 29:55.261
Great. Thank you.
Yeah.

29:55.294 --> 29:57.029
Oh, and one other thing.

29:57.063 --> 29:58.831
Lay off the political talk.

30:00.399 --> 30:02.401
Company policy.

30:03.202 --> 30:04.336
You got it.

30:07.106 --> 30:09.041
[BUZZING]

30:12.511 --> 30:14.080
Right.

30:18.350 --> 30:21.988
Facet A, 17.34 millimeters.

30:23.155 --> 30:26.458
Facet B, 17.29 millimeters.

30:29.028 --> 30:30.462
ED:
Did you get written up?

30:30.496 --> 30:32.431
No, I just got into
a little scrape last night.

30:32.464 --> 30:34.233
Now, I'm on substance watch.

30:34.266 --> 30:36.535
Well, it beats pissing in a cup
every 48 hours.

30:36.568 --> 30:37.970
LENNY:
Yeah.

30:38.004 --> 30:40.106
You weren't drunk though,
right?

30:40.139 --> 30:42.441
No. I was just distracted.

30:42.474 --> 30:43.842
Like I told you.

30:47.446 --> 30:51.217
Is that new?
When'd they put that up?

30:51.250 --> 30:53.886
[***]

30:55.221 --> 30:57.523
LENNY:
Yeah, that is kind of freaky.

30:57.556 --> 30:59.959
Is that a body?

31:01.027 --> 31:02.194
It's a dummy.

31:02.228 --> 31:04.363
It's just an ad.

31:04.396 --> 31:07.033
Shock value probably.

31:07.066 --> 31:09.301
Who are the Others?

31:09.335 --> 31:11.603
That's what I wanna know.

31:11.637 --> 31:14.240
LENNY:
If you're an Other, I think
you know you're an Other.

31:14.273 --> 31:17.176
Like, they know
who they are, for sure.

31:19.411 --> 31:22.681
Come on, guys.
Does it really matter?

31:22.714 --> 31:25.985
I mean, are we really talking
about killing people here?

31:26.018 --> 31:28.687
This morning,
my next-door neighbor,

31:28.720 --> 31:32.124
he just face-plants this girl
in the street for no reason.

31:32.158 --> 31:33.592
I mean, it was--
You know her?

31:33.625 --> 31:36.328
No, I didn't have to know her.
It was horrible--

31:36.362 --> 31:39.966
Hey, look, guys,
what if one of us was an Other?

31:39.999 --> 31:42.201
What do you think we'd do?

31:42.234 --> 31:45.671
You think
we'd turn each other in?

